Gnathosoma
.

CHELICERA (
Figures 1C & D
): movable digit 16 (14–17) long, bearing a tooth; fixed digit 16 (15–18) long, with two teeth and only with a tiny pilus dentilis near second tooth. PALP (
Figure 11A
): trochanter devoid of setae; femur with a strong and columnar seta and three simple setae; genu bearing a spatulate and four simple setae; tibia with simple setae; division between tibia and tarsus undiscernible; tarsal apotele 2-tined. HYPO- STOME (
Figure 12A
): weakly sclerotized with only two pairs of hypostomal setae (
h1
and 
h2
) and a row of tiny denticles; deutosternal groove faint.

Gnathosoma

. CHELICERA. (
Figure 7D
): with movable digit 29 (27–32) long, bearing a tooth; fixed digit 27 (25–28) long, bearing five visible teeth, pilus dentilis 6 (6–7) long, located at fourth tooth. PALP (
Figure 11D
): trochanter with two setae; femur with a spatulate seta and four simple setae; genu with two stouts and four simple setae; tibia with simple setae; tarsal apotele 2-tined as in deutonymph. HYPOSTOME (
Figure 12D
): with three pairs of hypostomal setae (
h1
, 
h2
and 
h3
) and one pair of palpcoxal setae (
pc
). Deutosternal groove with seven rows of denticles; corniculi horn-like.
